sequenceDiagram
    participant User as External User
    participant Gateway as data-science-gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant MLflow as MLflow Server<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS<br/>service-ca TLS
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS
    participant PG as PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP TLS optional
    participant S3 as S3-compatible Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over User,S3: Flow 1: External User Access via Gateway
    User->>Gateway: HTTPS/443<br/>Platform auth (OIDC/OAuth)
    Gateway->>MLflow: HTTPS/8443<br/>TLS (re-encrypted, service-ca)<br/>Forwarded user identity
    MLflow->>K8sAPI: HTTPS/6443<br/>SelfSubjectAccessReview<br/>Impersonated user token
    K8sAPI-->>MLflow: Authorization decision<br/>(experiments, datasets, registeredmodels)
    MLflow-->>Gateway: API Response
    Gateway-->>User: JSON Response

    Note over MLflow,PG: Flow 2: Backend Store Access
    MLflow->>PG: PostgreSQL/5432 or MySQL/3306<br/>TLS optional (PGSSLMODE=verify-full)<br/>Connection string credentials
    PG-->>MLflow: Query results<br/>(experiments, runs, models)

    Note over MLflow,S3: Flow 3: Artifact Storage Access
    MLflow->>S3: HTTPS/443 or HTTP/9000<br/>TLS via combined CA bundle<br/>AWS IAM credentials
    S3-->>MLflow: Model artifacts, plots, files

    participant Operator as MLflow Operator<br/>controller-runtime
    participant Helm as Helm Chart<br/>(embedded)

    Note over Operator,K8sAPI: Flow 4: Operator Reconciliation
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Watch MLflow CRs<br/>HTTPS/6443<br/>Bearer Token (SA)
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: MLflow CR event
    Operator->>Helm: Render templates<br/>(in-process)
    Helm-->>Operator: Kubernetes manifests
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Server-Side Apply<br/>HTTPS/6443<br/>Bearer Token (SA)
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: Apply result
